1 A BILL for an Act to provide for a legislative management study relating to periodically
2 reconvened sessions of the legislative assembly.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
4 SECTION 1. LEGISLATIVE MANAGEMENT STUDY - PERIODICALLY RECONVENED
5 SESSIONS OF THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY. During the 2025-26 interim, the legislative
6 management shall consider studying the use of periodically reconvened sessions of the
7 legislative assembly. The study must include consideration of the legislative assembly
8 reconvening, as determined by legislative management, for three consecutive natural days
9 each month except for December, on a Friday, Saturday, and Sunday, and in addition up to
10 seven consecutive natural days each year. The study may include consideration of alternate
11 proposals for periodically reconvening and a review of the timing of the meeting of the
12 legislative assembly for organizational and orientation purposes. The legislative management
13 shall report its findings and recommendations, together with any legislation required to
14 implement the recommendations, to the seventieth legislative assembly.
